# General Provisions
corplaw-fish-oprs-title = BROSB: Basic Rights of Sapient Beings
corplaw-fish-oprs-desc =
    The Basic Rights of Sapient Beings (BROSB) on NanoTrasen corporate territory take precedence over all other laws and codes of conduct.

    Protection mechanism. Security of a NanoTrasen facility is obliged to respect and protect the basic rights of all sapient beings present on NanoTrasen territory. Everyone has the right to seek protection of their basic rights from the command staff and the Internal Affairs Agent, who must assist within their competence. When those avenues are ineffective or objectively impossible, a person is entitled to contact Central Command by any available means.

    Right to life. No one may take a life without a decision by the court, the Captain, or Central Command. Liquidation is a last resort reserved for exceptional cases. Everyone has the right to cloning; no one may be deprived of it, even members of a hostile corporation. Refusal to clone is equivalent to murder.

    Right to dignity. A moral category denoting respect and self-respect of a sapient person. No one may be forced into actions that humiliate their dignity. No one may be subjected to medical, scientific or other experiments without voluntary consent.

    Right to freedom and personal inviolability. Surveillance and deprivation of liberty are only permitted by decision of Central Command or Security in connection with a violation of Corporate Law, quarantine actions, or an emergency.

    Right to privacy. No one is obliged to disclose or transmit information about their private life.

    Right to healthcare and medical assistance. Includes the right to euthanasia in case of severe illness.

    Right to property. No one may seize property unless it is contraband or its possession is otherwise prohibited by law.

    Presumption of innocence. Everyone charged with an offense has the right to be considered innocent until their guilt is established by a lawful public proceeding that provides every opportunity for defense.

    Freedom of religion. Religious associations are separate from the corporation and equal before its law.

    Violations of the rights of sapient beings are punished under the specific Corporate Law article covering the violation. Any being that has acquired sapience (e.g., through R&D experiments, space magic or an anomaly) is an object of research and is not protected by BROSB until the Research Director, the Captain, or Central Command decides otherwise on a case-by-case basis. Creators are responsible for sapient beings they create.

    Corporate Law is the primary law on corporate facilities and takes precedence over any other laws of local or planetary governments. Every sapient being on the station is required to comply with Corporate Law.

corplaw-fish-sentences-title = General Sentencing Guidelines
corplaw-fish-sentences-desc =
    - Violation of [color=#64d2ff]1XX[/color] articles — sentence from [color=#64d2ff]5[/color] to [color=#64d2ff]7[/color] minutes, or a warning.
    - Violation of [color=#32ade6]2XX[/color] articles — sentence from [color=#32ade6]10[/color] to [color=#32ade6]15[/color] minutes.
    - Violation of [color=#0a84ff]3XX[/color] articles — sentence from [color=#0a84ff]17[/color] to [color=#0a84ff]25[/color] minutes.
    - Violation of [color=#af52de]4XX[/color] articles — sentence from [color=#af52de]40[/color] to [color=#af52de]45[/color] minutes.
    - Violation of [color=#ff2d55]5XX[/color] articles — permanent imprisonment.

# 1xx Articles
corplaw-fish-art100-title = Offensive Conduct
corplaw-fish-art100-desc = Humiliation of the honor and dignity of another person in an indecent form.

corplaw-fish-art101-title = Minor Harm to Health
corplaw-fish-art101-desc = Causing non-life-threatening physical harm: minor injuries, bruises, cuts.

corplaw-fish-art102-title = Damage to Property
corplaw-fish-art102-desc = Deliberate or negligent damage to property of individuals or the corporation.

corplaw-fish-art103-title = Petty Theft
corplaw-fish-art103-desc = Illegal possession of low-value property or common-use property.

corplaw-fish-art104-title = Possession of Regulated Substances
corplaw-fish-art104-desc = Storage or use of controlled substances without permission outside medical purposes.

corplaw-fish-art105-title = Equipment Abuse
corplaw-fish-art105-desc = Misuse of equipment or excessive hoarding of gear.

corplaw-fish-art106-title = Interference with Crew Duties
corplaw-fish-art106-desc = Actions that impede crew members from performing their duties normally.

corplaw-fish-art107-title = Trespassing
corplaw-fish-art107-desc = Being in a low-importance area without the required access.

corplaw-fish-art109-title = Defamation
corplaw-fish-art109-desc = Spreading false information damaging to reputation.

# 2xx Articles
corplaw-fish-art200-title = Insulting Authority
corplaw-fish-art200-desc = Insulting corporate authority figures in a manner that undermines their authority.

corplaw-fish-art201-title = Moderate Harm to Health
corplaw-fish-art201-desc = Causing physical harm that requires medical intervention and temporary loss of working capacity.

corplaw-fish-art202-title = Vandalism
corplaw-fish-art202-desc = Deliberate damage to technical equipment, infrastructure, and station systems.

corplaw-fish-art204-title = Trafficking of Regulated Substances
corplaw-fish-art204-desc = Distributing controlled substances outside medical purposes.

corplaw-fish-art205-title = Possession of Combat Gear
corplaw-fish-art205-desc = Possession of dangerous items, self-defense tools, or improvised weapons without a permit.

corplaw-fish-art206-title = Obstruction of Justice
corplaw-fish-art206-desc = Actions that obstruct the administration of justice or the work of Security.

corplaw-fish-art207-title = Breaking and Entering
corplaw-fish-art207-desc = Illegal entry using force or tools to bypass obstacles.

corplaw-fish-art208-title = Animal Cruelty
corplaw-fish-art208-desc = Unauthorized killing of a non-aggressive animal.

corplaw-fish-art209-title = Negligence
corplaw-fish-art209-desc = Failure to perform or improper performance of duties due to carelessness.

corplaw-fish-art211-title = Espionage
corplaw-fish-art211-desc = Unlawful gathering of confidential corporate information to its detriment.

# 3xx Articles
corplaw-fish-art300-title = Strike
corplaw-fish-art300-desc = Organized cessation of work without the corporation's approval.

corplaw-fish-art301-title = Severe Harm to Health
corplaw-fish-art301-desc = Causing a serious threat to life: severe injuries, organ damage, fractures.

corplaw-fish-art302-title = Sabotage
corplaw-fish-art302-desc = Malicious obstruction of the normal operation of a department or the facility as a whole.

corplaw-fish-art303-title = Theft
corplaw-fish-art303-desc = Deliberate and unlawful possession of someone else's property.

corplaw-fish-art304-title = Contraband Trafficking
corplaw-fish-art304-desc = Storage, distribution, and sale of prohibited items.

corplaw-fish-art305-title = Possession of Non-Lethal Weapons
corplaw-fish-art305-desc = Possession of non-lethal weapons without proper authorization.

corplaw-fish-art306-title = Major Obstruction of Justice or Fraud
corplaw-fish-art306-desc = Deception, obstruction of investigations, concealment of evidence, intimidation of witnesses.

corplaw-fish-art307-title = Trespassing in a Strategic Area
corplaw-fish-art307-desc = Unauthorized entry into an area of strategic importance.

corplaw-fish-art308-title = Release of Flora and Fauna
corplaw-fish-art308-desc = Actions aimed at spreading aggressive flora and fauna.

corplaw-fish-art309-title = Discrediting
corplaw-fish-art309-desc = Spreading false information causing loss of trust in a person or organization.

corplaw-fish-art310-title = Kidnapping
corplaw-fish-art310-desc = Illegal deprivation of liberty for the purposes of detention, ransom, or commission of crimes.

corplaw-fish-art311-title = Anti-Corporate Espionage
corplaw-fish-art311-desc = Gathering of confidential information to undermine corporate interests.

corplaw-fish-art312-title = Violence Against Authority
corplaw-fish-art312-desc = Deliberate violence against authority representatives in the line of duty.

# 4xx Articles
corplaw-fish-art400-title = Failure to Comply During Emergency / Violation of Emergency or CTO Regimes
corplaw-fish-art400-desc = Refusal or evasion of lawful orders from authority figures during an emergency, or violation of emergency or counter-terror-operation regimes.

corplaw-fish-art401-title = Murder
corplaw-fish-art401-desc = Deliberately causing the death of a sapient being.

corplaw-fish-art402-title = Major Sabotage
corplaw-fish-art402-desc = Deliberate actions aimed at destroying key infrastructure components of the facility.

corplaw-fish-art403-title = Grand Theft
corplaw-fish-art403-desc = Deliberate possession of property significantly exceeding the established threshold.

corplaw-fish-art404-title = Manufacturing of Regulated Substances
corplaw-fish-art404-desc = Manufacturing controlled substances outside medical purposes.

corplaw-fish-art405-title = Possession of Lethal Weapons
corplaw-fish-art405-desc = Illegal storage, use, or distribution of lethal weapons.

corplaw-fish-art406-title = Embezzlement of Corporate Assets
corplaw-fish-art406-desc = Illegal appropriation or misuse of corporate resources.

corplaw-fish-art408-title = Cruelty to Special Animals
corplaw-fish-art408-desc = Deliberate harm to domestic, personal, or rare animals.

corplaw-fish-art409-title = Gross Negligence
corplaw-fish-art409-desc = Severe criminal inaction leading to critical damage.

corplaw-fish-art410-title = Kidnapping of a Head
corplaw-fish-art410-desc = Seizure and detention of a person holding the position of department head.

corplaw-fish-art411-title = Destruction of Borgs and AI
corplaw-fish-art411-desc = Deliberate destruction or disruption of cyborgs and the station AI.

corplaw-fish-art412-title = Seizure of Authority Weapons and/or Equipment
corplaw-fish-art412-desc = Illegal seizure or appropriation of the service weapon, special equipment, or gear of an authority representative.

# 5xx Articles
corplaw-fish-art500-title = Mutiny
corplaw-fish-art500-desc = Joining with crew members for an aggressive action against corporate policy.

corplaw-fish-art501-title = Body Destruction
corplaw-fish-art501-desc = Complete destruction of a sapient being's body resulting in loss of life and identity.

corplaw-fish-art502-title = Terrorism
corplaw-fish-art502-desc = Deliberate violent action with the aim of intimidation or achieving political goals.

corplaw-fish-art503-title = High-Value Theft
corplaw-fish-art503-desc = Deliberate possession of items of strategic value.

corplaw-fish-art504-title = Trafficking of Enemy Equipment
corplaw-fish-art504-desc = Storage, distribution, and sale of equipment used against corporate interests.

corplaw-fish-art505-title = Weapons Distribution
corplaw-fish-art505-desc = Manufacturing, sale, or transfer of weapons without proper permits.

corplaw-fish-art506-title = Discrediting the Corporation by an Authority Representative
corplaw-fish-art506-desc = Public actions by an authority representative that undermine the authority of the corporation, its bodies, or its officials.

corplaw-fish-art507-title = Intrusion into a Protected Strategic Area
corplaw-fish-art507-desc = Unauthorized entry into an area of heightened security and strategic significance.

corplaw-fish-art509-title = Abuse of Office by a High-Ranking Person
corplaw-fish-art509-desc = Use of official rights and power by a high-ranking person contrary to the interests of service and for selfish ends.

corplaw-fish-art510-title = Kidnapping of a High-Ranking Person
corplaw-fish-art510-desc = Seizure and detention of a particularly valuable organic asset of NanoTrasen against their will.

corplaw-fish-art511-title = Disclosure of Classified Information
corplaw-fish-art511-desc = Illegal or negligent disclosure of strategic classified information of NanoTrasen.

corplaw-fish-art512-title = Murder and/or Body Destruction of an Authority Representative
corplaw-fish-art512-desc = Deliberately causing the death of an authority representative in the line of duty, or destruction/concealment/desecration of their body.

# Circumstances (Mitigating)
corplaw-fish-circ-necessity-title = Extreme Necessity (Self-Defense)
corplaw-fish-circ-necessity-desc = Forced actions for self-defense, protecting the lives of colleagues, and station integrity. Charges dropped and immediate release.

corplaw-fish-circ-selfsurrender-title = Self-Surrender
corplaw-fish-circ-selfsurrender-desc = Voluntary personal appearance to Security before being formally charged or suspected.

corplaw-fish-circ-cooperation-title = Plea Bargain
corplaw-fish-circ-cooperation-desc = Disclosing full details of the crime, surrendering accomplices, and assisting in recovering stolen property. Information must be truthful.

corplaw-fish-circ-admission-title = Admission of Guilt
corplaw-fish-circ-admission-desc = Voluntary admission of guilt before or at the first interrogation. Does not apply to official misconduct. Does not stack with self-surrender.

corplaw-fish-circ-nointent-title = Lack of Intent
corplaw-fish-circ-nointent-desc = Investigation-confirmed lack of intent to commit the alleged crime.

corplaw-fish-circ-prisonerthreat-title = Imminent Threat to Prisoner
corplaw-fish-circ-prisonerthreat-desc = Imminent threat to the brig and the lives of prisoners. Immediate release; the prisoner must be moved to a safe location.

corplaw-fish-circ-medicalreason-title = Medical Reasons
corplaw-fish-circ-medicalreason-desc = Prisoner requires urgent medical attention. Even if self-inflicted, the modifier applies after first aid is given.

# Circumstances (Aggravating)
corplaw-fish-circ-officialmisconduct-title = Official Misconduct
corplaw-fish-circ-officialmisconduct-desc = Violation of Corporate Law by an official who is expected to set an example.

corplaw-fish-circ-nonviolentresistance-title = Non-Violent Resistance to Arrest
corplaw-fish-circ-nonviolentresistance-desc = Attempting to break out of cuffs and flee without harming anyone.

corplaw-fish-circ-violentresistance-title = Violent Resistance to Arrest
corplaw-fish-circ-violentresistance-desc = Use of force and/or weapons against Security during detention. Does not stack with non-violent resistance.

corplaw-fish-circ-aidabetting-title = Aiding and/or Abetting
corplaw-fish-circ-aidabetting-desc = Knowingly aiding a criminal or inciting a crime. Accomplices receive the articles they incited.

corplaw-fish-circ-attempt-title = Attempted Crime
corplaw-fish-circ-attempt-desc = Attempting to commit a crime (e.g., attempted murder).

corplaw-fish-circ-threat-title = Threatening to Commit a Crime
corplaw-fish-circ-threat-desc = Threatening to commit a violation (e.g., threatening mutiny).
